 of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Robert de Neufbourg was born in 1225, in Neufbourg, Seine-Maritime, Normandy, France, his father, Henry III de Neufbourg, Seigneur de Livarot, was 35 and his mother, Isabelle Malet, was 30. He married Marguerite de Ferrers about 1253. They were the parents of at least 2 daughters. He died in 1296, in France, at the age of 71."},"et":{"1225–1296":"1225–1296","1236–1287":"1236–1287","1250–1290":"1250–1290","1253–Female":"1253–Surnud","1190–1279":"1190–1279","1195–Female":"1195–Surnud","1190":"1190","18 May 1279":"18. mai 1279","1253":"1253","1296":"1296","1250":"1250","1195":"1195","before 1228":"enne 1228","1290":"1290","1225":"1225","1236":"1236","20 May 1287":"20. mai 1287","1279":"1279","Abt 1253":"umbes 1253","1287":"1287","Neufbourg, Seine-Maritime, Normandy, France":"Neufbourg, Seine-Maritime, Normandie, Prantsusmaa","Blainville, Seine-Maritime, Normandy, France":"Blainville, Seine-Maritime, Normandie, Prantsusmaa","France":"Prantsusmaa","Chanteloup, Manche, Normandy, France":"Chanteloup, Manche, Normandie, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1225–1296":"1225–1296","1236–1287":"1236–1287","1250–1290":"1250–1290","1253–Female":"1253–Kuollut","1190–1279":"1190–1279","1195–Female":"1195–Kuollut","1190":"1190","18 May 1279":"18. toukokuuta 1279","1253":"1253","1296":"1296","1250":"1250","1195":"1195","before 1228":"ennen vuotta 1228","1290":"1290","1225":"1225","1236":"1236","20 May 1287":"20. toukokuuta 1287","1279":"1279","Abt 1253":"noin 1253","1287":"1287","Neufbourg, Seine-Maritime, Normandy, France":"Neufbourg, Seine-Maritime